    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-15T12:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-15T12:45:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-15T12:00:00-05:45"
                            >February 15, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. My 47, February 10 [<hi rend="italic">13</hi>], 2 p.m. Press of this morning
                    publishes telegram from Guatemalan Minister for Foreign Affairs to Nicaraguan
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs offering the use of airplane to bring to Guatemala
                    on February 18 Nicaraguan delegates to Central American Conference.</p>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs has just informed me that this telegram crossed
                    telegram sent yesterday by President Sacasa to Presidents of other Central
                    American states proposing March 15th as date of Conference.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Central American missions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
